Common Nouns for Places

These words name different kinds of places.

bank, hotel, library, museum, mall, theater, hospital
airport, gas station, park, farm, zoo, factory, nursery
school, university, office, mosque, temple, shop, gym
post office, police station, restaurant, supermarket
stadium, synagogue, church


Common Nouns for People and Their Jobs

These words name people by the job or role they do.

singer, manager, sailor, gardener
dancer, secretary, pilot, police officer
artist, teacher, driver, plumber
photographer, doctor, writer, farmer
magician, dentist, friend, clerk
athlete, lawyer, brother, technician


Proper Nouns

Proper nouns are the names of specific people, places, or things. A proper noun always begins with a capital letter.


Names of People

These are examples of people's names, which are proper nouns.

Robin Hood, Florence Nightingale, Mom, Miss Park
Aladdin, Muhammad Ali, Dad, Mrs. Taylor
Frankenstein, George Washington, Granny, Mr. Young
Harry Potter, David Beckham, Grandad, Dr. Lee
Santa Claus, Julia Roberts, Uncle David, Professor Raj
Mahatma Gandhi, Nelson Mandela, Aunt Diana, Jose
Confucius, Alex Rodriguez, Ms. Hall, Yang Ming


Days of the Week and Months of the Year

The names of the days of the week and the months of the year are also proper nouns.

Days of the Week      Months of the Year
